cts. This theory develops the fundamentals for a coherent description of simple and complex, new and old media as well as diverse media constellations. Alongside the conceptual categorisation of various approaches to media theory, this study is also equally concerned with natural, artificial, individual, and digital media, as well as mass media. In this book, Julia Genz and Paul Gévaudan deliver a foundational, interdisciplinary work, that is sure to be of interest for both experts and students, and for a broader readership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCoding theory. 0aCommunication models. 0aCommunicationxMethodology. 0aIntermediality. 0aMass mediaxMethodology. 0aMultimedia communicationsxMethodology. 0aPerformance artxMethodology. 4aCharles Sanders Peirce. 4aFerdinand De Saussure. 4aIntermedialität. 4aKoch/Oesterreicher. 4aKommunikationsmodelle. 4aMcLuhan. 4aMedien. 4aMedientheorie. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aMedienästhetik. 4aMultimedialität. 4aSemiose. 4aSemiotik. 4aShannon/Weaver. 4aSprache. 4aTransmedialität. 4aUmberto Eco. 4aWittgenstein. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aCommunication Models.  aFerdinand De Saussure.  aIntermediality.  aKoch/oesterreicher.  aLanguage.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia Theory.  aMedia.  aMultimediality.  aSemiosis.  aSemiotics.  aShannon/weaver.  aTransmediality.  aUmberto Eco.  aWittgenstein.1 aGévaudan, Paul, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2016z9783110485332oZDB-23-DSW08